value.0: Tragedy and suffering stitched together in perfect, ugly precision. The magnificent ruin is the culmination of dark knowledge and sacrifice.
Feverishly inspired, spreading the new knowledge to all who will listen, this is the dark sage in his essence.

Value.value: You recall learning previously that Suhail Duskrise was one of the viziers of Swamprise Keep. From the mad ramblings on these pages, he must have fallen quite far.

The random ramblings on these pages are difficult to make out, but you are able to discern a few things. The passages describe a man named Suhail who lost his family abruptly and was tempted by an unknown power.
You recall a story told by the locals of Brost County - a tale of caution and woe about a former knight of the realm - Sir Fetton. They say he wielded a powerful blade infernal blade.

The letters on these pages are almost entirely faded, but you recognize the language as the Infernal script. One of the pages you are able to discern details the creation of an evil sword for a knightly champion of the Hells. First, the infernal smiths picked their metal up with tongs, they struck it with a heavy hammer, and then heated the metal by stoking the fires of Baator with a great bellows.
